(25, 15, 1, '', '2014-11-20 09:16:34', 680, 2523, '05ce349ee1a39196646bf4449d0c53d6b8e64f3b', '{"id":15,"asset_id":83,"title":"Venison preperation tips","alias":"venison-preperation-tips","introtext":"<p> Venison is very easy to prepare and can be eaten as steaks, roasts, stews, sausages, patties, minced meat, biltong and dry wors. Marinating venison is great for flavouring but it should not be left to marinate for longer than 2 hours for smaller pieces like steaks, and 12 hours for larger pieces<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Venison is more watery than beef so it\\u2019s important to keep the water inside! When grilling a good cut of veni- son, the meat must be cooked rapidly using a higher heat than used for beef. The goal is to sear the outside of the venison whilst keeping the inside rare or medium rare. The surface should be basted regularly and the meat left for 5 minutes after being removed from the heat.Cooking less tender cuts of venison should be done through slow-cooking, stewing, marinating and drizzling the meat with fat from other sources.<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"2","created":"2014-11-20 09:16:34","created_by":"680","created_by_alias":"","modified":"","modified_by":null,"checked_out":null,"checked_out_time":null,"publish_up":"2014-11-20 09:16:34","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_paren