(99, 24, 1, '', '2014-12-11 12:33:46', 680, 3448, 'f27e94f8aeeaa7267abc18449b21f98e6416c224', '{"id":24,"asset_id":"105","title":"CHILLI AND GINGER VENISON IN LEATTUCE LEAVES","alias":"chilli-and-ginger-venison-in-leattuce-leaves","introtext":"<p>CHILLI AND GINGER VENISON IN LEATTUCE LEAVES This recipe is based on the Thai dish of minced meat cooked with chilli, ginger and garlic then stuffed into crunchy lettuce leaves. It works very well with venison as this fast cooking method KEEPS it deliciously moist and tender. The \\u201cgameyness\\u201d goes perfectly with these exciting flavours. If lettuce isn''t satisfying enough for you, this recipe can be enjoyed with noodles or rice too. INGREDIENTS [SERVES 4] 1 tbsp flavourless oil 600g minced venison 1 tbsp sesame oil 3 cloves garlic, peeled and crushed 4cm ginger, peeled and finely grated 2 red chillies, deseeded and finely chopped 1 small tin water chestnuts, finely chopped 4 spring onions, trimmed, finely sliced 2 tbsp soy sauce 1 tbsp fish sauce Pinch of brown sugar 1 lime, juiced 1 bunch coriander, finely chopped Pinch of salt Lettuce leaves INSTRUCTIONS: 1. Heat the flavourless oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat, add the mince, season with salt, and fry, stirring with a wooden spoon to break up lumps, until it is nicely coloured. Lift the meat out with a slotted spoon and set aside. 2. Add the sesame oil to the pan and the garlic, ginger and chilli, and cook for 2-3 minutes, stirring constantly. Return the meat to the pan and stir thoroughly to get all the ingredients well acquainted. Add the water chestnuts and spring onions, stir well to combine, and heat through. 3. Stir in the fish and soy sauces, a pinch of brown sugar, the lime juice and the coriander, and once the mixture is hot, remove from the heat and place in a serving bowl. Serve with a big pile of lettuce leaves to stuff the mince into.<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"2","created":"2014-12-11 10:25:22","created_by":"680","crea